children.value: You can't plough a field by turning it over in your mind!

children.name: Text
children.value: Complacency is the father of ignorance.

children.name: Text
children.value: Peace flowers want water more days than one.

children.name: Text
children.value: When we stop working, we stop living…

children.name: Text
children.value: Bad news is, that's not the hardest part…

children.name: Text
children.value: In it for yourself, or for all of us?!

children.name: Text
children.value: The only choice is the right choice!

children.name: Text
children.value: You've got something for me, haven't you?

children.name: Text
children.value: Brought this tiresome business to a close?

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't just sit there, hand it in!

children.name: Text
children.value: Yes, you're hard working, but impatient!

children.name: Text
children.value: Give me some time can't you?

children.name: Text
children.value: Didn't I tell you, I don't have anything!

children.name: Text
children.value: Didn't you say you'd provide me an escort?

children.name: Text
children.value: Help an old man across the sea won't you?

children.name: Text
children.value: I take a few good people wherever I go.

children.name: Text
children.value: Don't let them judge you by your father's actions; you're your own person.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even if your father was a traitor, I won't judge you before I know you.

children.name: Text
children.value: I hear you're building warships—arms dealer to the Empire…

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't like what goes on in that prison any more than you do.

children.name: Text
children.value: A little bird tells me you're meeting Isabel? There's a woman who understands progress.

children.name: Text
children.value: Isabel remains fundamentally good. You can trust her to seek out truth.

children.name: Text
children.value: No greater punishment exists for your Uncle Edvard than a fair trial.

children.name: Text
children.value: Bring an end to this age of terror!

children.name: Text
children.value: Two flawed men. But there was good in them, as there is in you.

children.name: Text
children.value: Where's my ear trumpet? Want me to do what? You must be out of your mind.

children.name: Text
children.value: I know what it's like to have to choose. Whatever you decide, stick by it.

children.name: Text
children.value: Just let me be, I'm fine! All I need is my goddamn walking cane!

children.name: Text
children.value: I wish a few others could have seen this.

children.name: Text
children.value: Makes me want to believe again.

children.name: Text
children.value: Life doesn't seem so wretched now.

children.name: Text
children.value: Sun's out from behind the cloud.

children.name: Text
children.value: Seems I'm one of the lucky ones.

children.name: Text
children.value: I've met so many worse than you.

children.name: Text
children.value: I see you have a heart.

children.name: Text
children.value: You incline to what is right.

children.name: Text
children.value: Then the bad old days are back.

children.name: Text
children.value: Even now, the same damn bunk!

children.name: Text
children.value: Did I hear that nonsense right?!

children.name: Text
children.value: Oh I don't hate you, I just don't like you.

children.name: Text
children.value: I don't stoop to hate, but you run me close.

children.name: Text
children.value: Better than some is still worse than most.

children.name: Text
children.value: I find your whole standpoint supremely questionable.

children.name: Text
children.value: Your moral compass goes south fast.

children.name: Text
children.value: You're blind as a mole, and just as dirty.

children.name: Text
children.value: I'm not the type to think all people bad, so let's just wait and see how you go.

children.name: Text
children.value: You can't get on the wrong side of me, not if you're on the right side.

children.name: Text
children.value: What you say your name was? That's a strong name, don't let it down.

children.name: Text
children.value: Been known by George Smith so long, no use changing now.

children.name: Text
children.value: Are you trying to knock my door in?
